	<h4>What does it do?</h4>

	<p>This field definition can be used to add <strong>Categories</strong> to a LISE instance. You can use <strong>Categories</strong> to filter your items for frontend views.</p>

	<p><strong>Categories</strong> have some restrictions. You can have only one of these per LISE instance. Others will be ignored.</p>


	<h4>How do I use it?</h4>

	<p>After you create the <strong>Categories</strong> field definition, a new tab will appear where you can create your desired <strong>Categories</strong>. If you want you can reorder them afterwards.</p>

	<p>The settings for this field are:</p>

	<ul>
		<li><b>Sub Type:</b>
			<ul>
				<li>Dropdown</li>
				<li>Multi Select</li>
				<li>Radio Group</li>
				<li>Checkbox Group</li>
				<li>jQuery MultiSelect</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
  		<li><b>Separator</b></li>
  		<li><b>Columns</b></li>
  		<li><b>Size</b></li>
	</ul>

</div>